d": 506}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3718"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "JAK3", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9935524463653564, "span": {"begin": 592, "end": 596}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3718"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "JAK3 kinase", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9842697381973267, "span": {"begin": 620, "end": 631}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cell types", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.49016010761260986, "span": {"begin": 686, "end": 696}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.96354740858078, "span": {"begin": 745, "end": 749}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5925"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "RB1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9496635794639587, "span": {"begin": 751, "end": 754}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3716"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "JAK", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9922014474868774, "span": {"begin": 767, "end": 770}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6646"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "STAT", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9844397306442261, "span": {"begin": 771, "end": 775}}, {"id": ["mesh:D001169"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "collagen-induced arthritis", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9478996992111206, "span": {"begin": 857, "end": 883}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1280"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "collagen", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9805050492286682, "span": {"begin": 857, "end": 865}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9798939824104309, "span": {"begin": 884, "end": 888}}], "text": "Janus tyrosine kinase (JAK) 3 is a member of the JAK family that is constitutively associated with the Box-1 region of the cytokine receptor intracellular domain. JAK3 is activated upon ligand-induced receptor dimerization (Stahl, et al. 1994).  The PF-06651600 selective JAK3 inhibitor is undergoing phase 2 clinical evaluation for use in treating rheumatoid arthritis. This compound inhibits JAK3 kinase activity with an IC50 of 33.1 nM (IC50 &gt; 10000 nM). It lacks activity against JAK1, JAK2, or TYK2 (Telliez, et al. 2016, Thorarensen, et al. 2017). The RB1 novel and highly selective JAK3 inhibitor&nbsp; blocks JAK3 kinase in vitro and abrogates functional activity in various cell types (Pei, et al. 2018). When orally administered to mice, RB1 mediate the JAK-STAT pathway and reduces the clinical and microscopic manifestations of paw damage in collagen-induced arthritis mice.", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 21:46:38 +0000 2026"}